<div class="legal-section">
  <h2>1. What Payxem Does</h2>
  <p>Payxem is an invoicing and financial tracking platform. We enable users to create invoices, send payment links, track payments, and manage earnings.</p>
  <p>Payments are processed through third-party providers such as PayPal and Stripe. Payxem does not operate as a bank or licensed financial institution.</p>
</div>

<div class="legal-section">
  <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We collect information to provide and improve our services.</p>
  <h3>a. Information You Provide</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Name and profile details</li>
    <li>Email address</li>
    <li>Phone number (optional)</li>
    <li>Business or service information</li>
    <li>Bank or payout details (when provided)</li>
    <li>Identity verification information (for KYC, when required)</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>b. Transaction and Usage Data</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Invoice details (amounts, descriptions, client data)</li>
    <li>Payment records and statuses</li>
    <li>Wallet and ledger activity</li>
    <li>Withdrawal and payout requests</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>c. Device and Technical Data</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>IP address</li>
    <li>Browser type and device information</li>
    <li>Usage logs and activity within the platform</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>d. Cookies and Tracking</h3>
  <p>We use cookies and similar technologies to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Keep you logged in</li>
    <li>Improve performance</li>
    <li>Understand usage patterns</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="legal-section">
  <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <p>We use your data to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide and operate Payxem services</li>
    <li>Create and manage invoices and payment records</li>
    <li>Process withdrawals and payouts</li>
    <li>Verify identity (KYC where required)</li>
    <li>Improve platform performance and security</li>
    <li>Communicate important updates and support responses</li>
    <li>Prevent fraud, abuse, and unauthorized activity</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="legal-section">
  <h2>4. Payment Processing</h2>
  <p>All payments are handled by third-party providers such as PayPal and Stripe.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Payment data may be processed directly by these providers</li>
    <li>Payxem may receive payment status and transaction details</li>
    <li>Funds may be received into accounts designated by Payxem or its affiliated entities for settlement and distribution</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Payxem does not provide banking or custodial financial services.</p>
</div>

<div class="legal-section">
  <h2>5. Sharing of Information</h2>
  <p>We do not sell your personal data.</p>
  <p>We may share information with:</p>
  <h3>a. Payment Providers</h3>
  <p>To process transactions and verify payments.</p>
  <h3>b. Service Providers</h3>
  <p>Hosting, analytics, email delivery, and infrastructure services.</p>
  <h3>c. Identity Verification Partners</h3>
  <p>For KYC and compliance checks (when required).</p>
  <h3>d. Legal Requirements</h3>
  <p>If required by law, regulation, or to protect rights and safety.</p>
</div>

<div class="legal-section">
  <h2>6. Data Storage and Security</h2>
  <p>We implement industry-standard measures to protect your data, including:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Encrypted connections (HTTPS)</li>
    <li>Secure authentication and session management</li>
    <li>Access controls and monitoring</li>
    <li>Regular system updates</li>
  </ul>
  <p>However, no system is completely secure. You are responsible for keeping your login credentials safe.</p>
</div>

<div class="legal-section">
  <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
  <p>We retain your data as long as necessary to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide services</li>
    <li>Maintain financial and transaction records</li>
    <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
  </ul>
  <p>You may request deletion of your account, subject to legal and operational requirements.</p>
</div>

<div class="legal-section">
  <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access your personal data</li>
    <li>Update or correct information</li>
    <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
    <li>Object to certain data uses</li>
  </ul>
  <p>To make a request, contact us at: <a href="mailto:support@payxem.com">support@payxem.com</a></p>
</div>

<div class="legal-section">
  <h2>9. Third-Party Links and Services</h2>
  <p>Payxem may include links or integrations with third-party services.</p>
  <p>We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third parties. You should review their policies separately.</p>
</div>

<div class="legal-section">
  <h2>10. International Use</h2>
  <p>Payxem is designed for global use, including regions where traditional payment systems may be limited.</p>
  <p>By using Payxem, you acknowledge that your data may be processed in multiple countries where our services or partners operate.</p>
</div>

<div class="legal-section">
  <h2>11. Updates to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.</p>
  <p>Changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last updated" date. Continued use of the platform means you accept the updated policy.</p>
</div>

<div class="legal-section">
  <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, contact us at:</p>
  <p>Email: <a href="mailto:support@payxem.com">support@payxem.com</a></p>
</div>
